{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e29e811d-f297-44e6-820a-27b180fd59f8","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 **dropped support for `net6.0` and `net7.0`**. The supported target frameworks are:\n\n- **`net8.0`+** (for .NET)\n- **`net462`+** (for .NET Framework)\n\nYour project targets `net6.0`, so upgrading to MSTest v4 will fail. You need to **retarget to at least `net8.0`** first.\n\nNote that `net6.0` itself is already out of LTS support (ended November 2024), so upgrading the TFM is recommended regardless.\n\n**To upgrade**, you'd need to:\n1. Change `<TargetFramework>net6.0</TargetFramework>` → `net8.0` (or `net9.0`)\n2. Then update `MSTest` from `3.8.0` → `4.x`\n\nWant me to make these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5f56277c-0705-4054-86d7-f18afe4db288","outputTokens":228},"id":"d1bf1e86-fe9e-4da1-91e2-9a397c0f6d29","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:02:03.395Z","parentId":"22944cda-2f8d-455c-a106-cd65dca2b3ef"}
